Yep, you are probably right. Last time I thought about volcanoes goes a long way back. Probably primary school, most likely in some kind of art class.. can almost smell the drying gouache paint.

When I think of volcanoes, I picture a nice mountain cone with flames coming out at the top and lava running down its side, like chocolate running down the ice-cream on a hot summer days. Missing ice cream these days…

In Switzerland we don’t often come across volcanoes… We do we need to go abroad, but where? We will start by plotting a map of where to find volcanoes… and, if we are lucky, we will end our tour by witnessing a live eruption!

gt_table_data %>%
  select(volcano_name, country, number_eruptions, population_within_10_km) %>%
  gt() %>%
  tab_header(md("**Top 10 <span style='color:darkred'>volcanoes**</span>"),
             subtitle = "With the most eruptions in the last 10 years") %>%
  cols_label(
    volcano_name = md("**Volcano**"),
    country = md("**Country**"),
    number_eruptions =md("**Number of eruptions**"),
    population_within_10_km = md("**Population < 10km**")
  ) %>%

  fmt_number(
    columns = vars(population_within_10_km),
    decimals =0 ,
    use_seps = TRUE,
    sep_mark = "'",
  ) %>%
  tab_style(
    style = list(
      cell_fill(color = "darkred",

      columns = vars(number_eruptions),

  ) %>%

  tab_style(

# data for world map 1

eruption_days %>%
  filter(volcano_name %in% top10,
         start_year>1920) %>%
  group_by(volcano_name) %>%
  arrange(volcano_name) %>%
  arrange(date_start) %>%
  mutate(waiting=difftime(date_start,lag(date_start), units = "days"),
         number_eruptions=n() )%>%
  mutate(volcano_name=paste(volcano_name, " (",number_eruptions,")"))%>%

  ggplot(aes(y=fct_reorder(volcano_name, waiting,max),x=waiting, fill=volcano_name))+
  geom_density_ridges()+

  #geom_jitter(aes(size=vei),shape=2, colour="darkred", alpha=0.7)+
  scale_fill_viridis_d(option="magma", direction=1)+
  scale_x_continuous(labels=function(x) format(x, big.mark = "'", scientific = FALSE))+
  labs(
    title="Waiting time distribution",
    subtitle=" over the last 120 years for the most active 10 volcanoes",
    caption="source: The Smithsonian Institution.",
    x="Days",
    y="(Number of eruptions)",
    size="Volcanic Explosivity Index (VEI)"
  )+
  guides(fill=FALSE)+
  theme_light() +
  theme(
    legend.position = c(.75, .25),
    legend.background =element_rect(
      size=0.5, linetype="solid",

volc<-data.frame(x=c(1,0.5,0.25 ,0,-0.25,-0.5,-1), y=c(0,0.5,0.75,0.75,0.75,0.5,0))


lava<-data.frame(x=c(0.5,0.25,-0.25),y=c(0.5,0.75,0.75))

cone<-data.frame(x=c(1,0.25,0,-0.25,-1), y=c(0.5,1.5,1.75,1.5,0.5))



projectile<- function(velocity, angle,steps=0.1,y_0=0.75, g=9.81){
      angle_rad<-angle*pi/180

      time_to_target<- velocity*sin(angle_rad)/g+(sqrt(velocity*sin(angle_rad)*velocity*sin(angle_rad)+2*g*y_0)/g)
      time_to_target<-round(time_to_target,digit=1)
      time_steps<-seq(0,12,steps)
      x<-velocity*cos(angle_rad)*time_steps
      y<-y_0+velocity*sin(angle_rad)*time_steps-0.5*(g*time_steps*time_steps)

       #
answer<-tibble(tt=time_steps,xt=x,yt=y)

     return(answer)
 }


shots<-tibble(n_shots=seq(1,10,1),
              velo=c(runif(max(n_shots),2,7)),
              angl=   c(runif(max(n_shots),30,130)))

library(tidyverse)
volcano_animation<-shots %>%
  rowwise() %>%
  mutate(traj=list(projectile(velo,angl)) ) %>%
  unnest(cols = c(traj))  %>% 
  dplyr::select(n_shots,tt,xt,yt) %>% 

  ggplot() +
  geom_polygon(data=volc,aes(x = x, y = y))+
  geom_polygon(data=lava,aes(x = x, y = y), fill="red")+
  geom_point(aes(x=xt,y=yt, group=n_shots, colour=n_shots))+
  scale_color_viridis_c(begin=0.5, end=1,option="inferno")+
  coord_cartesian(xlim=c(-5,5),ylim=c(0,2))+
  theme_void()+
  theme(
    legend.position="",
    plot.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),

  )+


transition_reveal(along = tt) +
  shadow_wake(wake_length = 0.2, size = 2, alpha = FALSE, colour = 'grey92')

volcano_animation
